# Use with VS Code REST Client extension or IntelliJ HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Trigger Dexter Workflow (simulated JIRA comment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhook/jira
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "webhookEvent": "comment_created",
  "comment": {
    "body": "@dexter implement the change described in this ticket",
    "author": { "displayName": "Test Developer" }
  },
  "issue": { "key": "DXTR-2" }
}

### Non-dexter comment (should be ignored)
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhook/jira
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "webhookEvent": "comment_created",
  "comment": {
    "body": "This is a regular comment without the trigger",
    "author": { "displayName": "Product Manager" }
  },
  "issue": { "key": "TASK-789" }
}

### Non-comment event (should be ignored)
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhook/jira
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "webhookEvent": "issue_updated",
  "comment": {
    "body": "@dexter this won't trigger because event type is wrong",
    "author": { "displayName": "Test Developer" }
  },
  "issue": { "key": "TEST-001" }
}
